WHO response
There are six WHO 2030 global targets for soil-transmitted helminthiases:
achieve and maintain elimination of STH morbidity in pre-school and school age children;
reduce the number of tablets needed in preventive chemotherapy for STH;
increase domestic financial support to preventive chemotherapy for STH;
establish an efficient STH control programme in adolescent, pregnant and lactating women;
establish an efficient strongyloidiasis control programme in school age children; and
ensure universal access to at least basic sanitation and hygiene by 2030 in STH-endemic areas.
In order to achieve the 2030 NTD roadmap, WHO works with Member States and partners to achieve and maintain effective preventative chemotherapy coverage for STH in all at-risk groups, to measure the impact of the interventions in countries that have been implementing the programme for more than 5 years and to advocate for an integration of STH
